                ,----------------------------------------------------------------------------,
                |                    T3hb0t - A Python based IRC bot                         |
                '----------------------------------------------------------------------------'
                ,----------------------------------------------------------------------------,
                | 0x00 :                            Author                                   |
                '----------------------------------------------------------------------------'
                
                Puppynix, and of course my main man Optical ;) !
                
                ,----------------------------------------------------------------------------,
                | 0x01 :                            Info                                     |
                '----------------------------------------------------------------------------'
                
                T3hb0t is an IRC bot client capable of connecting to multiple servers
                and channels. Easily customized and easy to add commands.
                
                Default operator prefix is ! . Can be set with -o option. If using -i <pass>
                to identify, the nick must be registered beforehand (some servers require
                email activation !).
                
                ,----------------------------------------------------------------------------,
                | 0x02 :                            Help                                     |
                '----------------------------------------------------------------------------'
                
                Help can be found with the usual -h option, but here is the list of 
                commands/options anyways.
                
                Usage: T3hb0t.py [options]
                
                Options:
                  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
                  -r, --run             Start the bot with the saved settings (use -s to set
                                        settings)
                  -i IDENTIFY, --ident=IDENTIFY
                                        If set, the bot will try to identify with pass (must
                                        be run with -r). Usage: -i <pass>
                  -g, --get             Print the variables set
                  -c, --clear           Clear all variables
                  -j JUST, --just=JUST  Connect just to server with id. Usage: -j <id>
                  -o CMD_OP, --operator=CMD_OP
                                        Sets operator sign to be used as prefix to commands.
                                        Usage: -o <operator>
                  -d DEL_ID, --del=DEL_ID
                                        Deletes setting with id. Usage: -d <id>
                  -a ADD_ADMIN, --admin=ADD_ADMIN
                                        Adds admin to database. Usage: -a <username>
                                        <password>
                  -u USE, --use=USE     Starts bot with specified settings. Usage: -u <nick>
                                        <host> <port> <channels>
                  -s SET, --set=SET     Saves a setting. Usage: -s <id> <nick> <host> <port>
                                        <channels>